<section id="HotTaxTip" style="padding-bottom: 100px;">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6">
<div class="img" style="margin-top: 18%;"><img alt="img" src="assets/img/kmstaxtip.png" /></div>
<a class="btn btn-primary" href="#" style="margin-left: 35%;">Access our Km tracking</a></div>

<div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6">
<div class="about-text mb-0">
<h2 style="position: absolute;margin-top: -43px;margin-left: 57px;color:#799BFD;">Hot Tax Tip</h2>

<h3>Key Driver to get your best refund outcome</h3>

<p>Getting the most out of the tax refund systems. It&rsquo;s all about car Kms......Kms....Kms......Kms. Get this aspect of your tax deductions right will guarantee you the best possible tax refund.</p>

<div class="faq">
<ul class="accordion">
	<li class="accordion-item"><a class="accordion-title active" href="javascript:void(0)">Can I claim my motorcar for work related business?</a>

	<p class="accordion-content show">According to the tax office rules<br />
	Under the cents per Kilometre method a Police officer can claim a maximum of 5,000 business Kilometre&rsquo;s per car</p>
	</li>
	<li class="accordion-item"><a class="accordion-title" href="javascript:void(0)">What evidence do I need to make this claim?</a>
	<p class="accordion-content">You do not need written evidence to show how many Kilometres you have travelled, but we may ask you to show how you worked out your business Kilometre&rsquo;s(such as, calendar or diary records) or <u>better still get the Police Tax Phone App</u>.</p>
	</li>
	<li class="accordion-item"><a class="accordion-title" href="javascript:void(0)">What per kilometre rate can I claim?</a>
	<p class="accordion-content">The rate covers your running expenses and depreciation. If you use the cents per Kilometre method, your claim is based on a set rate for each business Kilometre travelled. The rate is 68 cents per Kilometre from the 2018&ndash;19 income year.</p>
	</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
